1. Windows module definition (.def) files

We generate these files manually.

Note: In all cases remove the `LIBRARY` line at the end of the generated .def
file because we don't need it.

See upstream/src/meson.build for the set of headers used in each case. For
example, the variable `hb_base_headers` is used for harfbuzz.def.

Generate libharfbuzz/libharfbuzz/harfbuzz.def like this:

  cd upstream/src
  ./gen-def.py ../../libharfbuzz/libharfbuzz/harfbuzz.def \
  hb-aat-layout.h \
  hb-aat.h \
  hb-blob.h \
  hb-buffer.h \
  hb-common.h \
  hb-deprecated.h \
  hb-draw.h \
  hb-face.h \
  hb-font.h \
  hb-map.h \
  hb-ot-color.h \
  hb-ot-deprecated.h \
  hb-ot-font.h \
  hb-ot-layout.h \
  hb-ot-math.h \
  hb-ot-meta.h \
  hb-ot-metrics.h \
  hb-ot-name.h \
  hb-ot-shape.h \
  hb-ot-var.h \
  hb-ot.h \
  hb-set.h \
  hb-shape-plan.h \
  hb-shape.h \
  hb-style.h \
  hb-unicode.h \
  hb.h \
  hb-ft.h

Generate libharfbuzz/libharfbuzz/harfbuzz-subset.def like this:

  cd upstream/src
  ./gen-def.py ../../libharfbuzz/libharfbuzz/harfbuzz-subset.def \
  hb-subset.h \
  hb-subset-repacker.h

Generate libharfbuzz/libharfbuzz/harfbuzz-icu.def like this:

  cd upstream/src
  ./gen-def.py ../../libharfbuzz/libharfbuzz/harfbuzz-icu.def \
  hb-icu.h
